Your project uses **MSTest v3 (3.8.0)** on **net8.0**. Here's what applies to your code:

### Breaking change found in your code

**`[ExpectedException]` removed** (lines 9, 16) — This attribute is gone in v4. Replace with `Assert.ThrowsExactly<T>()` inside the test body:

```csharp
// Before
[ExpectedException(typeof(ArgumentNullException))]
[TestMethod]
public void Validate_NullInput_ThrowsArgumentNull()
{
    Validate(null);
}

// After
[TestMethod]
public void Validate_NullInput_ThrowsArgumentNull()
{
    Assert.ThrowsExactly<ArgumentNullException>(() => Validate(null));
}
```

Same pattern applies to `Process_InvalidState_ThrowsInvalidOperation`.

### Other v4 breaking changes (not in your code, but good to know)

| Change | Fix |
|---|---|
| `Assert.ThrowsException` removed | Use `Assert.ThrowsExactly` |
| `ClassCleanupBehavior` enum removed | Remove the argument from `[ClassCleanup]` |
| `TestContext.Properties.Contains()` | Use `.ContainsKey()` |
| `[TestMethod("name")]` constructor changed | Use `DisplayName = "name"` |
| Custom `TestMethodAttribute.Execute` removed | Override `ExecuteAsync` instead |
| `TestTimeout.Infinite` removed | Use `int.MaxValue` |

### Behavioral changes to watch for

- **`TreatDiscoveryWarningsAsErrors`** now defaults to `true` — discovery warnings will fail the run.
- **`TestCase.Id`** generation changed — Azure DevOps test history may reset.
- **`TestContext.TestName`** throws if accessed in `[ClassInitialize]`.

